<subSubSection id="B6A56557FF98A272FF66517BFC8F838C" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="549" pageId="3" pageNumber="548" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FE0036DCFF98A272FF66517BFC8F838C" blockId="3.[151,1436,1704,2001]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,152,255]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="549" pageId="3" pageNumber="548">
<emphasis id="CCCBEACEFF98A275FF66517BFE9F842F" bold="true" box="[198,326,1858,1884]" pageId="3" pageNumber="548">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species similar to 
<taxonomicName id="39BF4D5FFF98A275FD8C517AFC12842E" authority="(Fallen, 1820)" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1820" box="[556,971,1859,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Elachiptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuta">
<emphasis id="CCCBEACEFF98A275FD8C517AFCC3842F" box="[556,794,1859,1884]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="548">Elachiptera cornuta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9A2E4B2DFF98A275FC8C517AFC1A842E" author="Fallen, C. L." box="[812,963,1859,1885]" pageId="3" pageNumber="548" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref3388" refString="Fallen, C. L. (1820) Oscinides Sveciae. Litteris Berlingianis, Lundae [= Lund], II + 1 - 10 pp." type="book chapter" year="1820">Fallén, 1820</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="39BF4D5FFF98A275FBA8517AFAFE842E" authority="Duda, 1932" authorityName="Duda" authorityYear="1932" box="[1032,1319,1859,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Elachiptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufifrons">
<emphasis id="CCCBEACEFF98A275FBA8517AFB56842F" box="[1032,1167,1859,1884]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="548">E. rufifrons</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="9A2E4B2DFF98A275FB39517AFAFE842E" author="Duda, O." box="[1177,1319,1859,1885]" pageId="3" pageNumber="548" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref3294" refString="Duda, O. (1932) 61. Chloropidae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaearktischen Region, 6 (1) (Lieferung 64). Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 48." type="book chapter" year="1932">Duda, 1932</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It can be distinguished from the former by the dusted line in the middle of the scutum, along the acrostichal setulae, the dusted prescutellar part of the scutum and the yellow hind corners of the ocellar triangle. Contrary to 
<taxonomicName id="39BF4D5FFF98A275FA2251A8FF2684A3" authorityName="Duda" authorityYear="1932" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Elachiptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="548" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufifrons">
<emphasis id="CCCBEACEFF98A275FA2251A8FA4D84D9" box="[1410,1428,1937,1962]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="548">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="CCCBEACEFF98A275FF37518EFF2684A3" box="[151,255,1975,2000]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="548">rufifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ocellar triangle of the new species is mostly black except for its hind corners, and the dusted stripe on the scutum is divided into 3 longitudinal lines: two wider ones along the dorsocentral setulae and a narrow one along the acrostichal setulae. Like 
<taxonomicName id="39BF4D5FFF9FA272FD6D5686FC2F83AB" authority="Duda, 1932" authorityName="Duda" authorityYear="1932" box="[717,1014,190,216]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Elachiptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="austriaca">
<emphasis id="CCCBEACEFF9FA272FD6D5686FD0683AB" box="[717,735,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="CCCBEACEFF9FA272FD505686FCB883AB" box="[752,865,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="549">austriaca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="9A2E4B2DFF9FA272FCCA5687FC2F83AB" author="Duda, O." box="[874,1014,190,216]" pageId="4" pageNumber="549" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref3294" refString="Duda, O. (1932) 61. Chloropidae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der Palaearktischen Region, 6 (1) (Lieferung 64). Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 48." type="book chapter" year="1932">Duda, 1932</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
the new species has only one long orbital seta, but differs from this species by its black thorax.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
